
     NAME
          icopen  - open a 'ic'-formatted file for reading/writing

     FORTRAN F77 SPECIFICATION
          integer function  icopen(iu,filename,acc)
          integer*4 iu
          character*7 filename
          character*1 acc

     PARAMETERS
          iu    = file unit, can range from 1 to 25
          file  = filename
          acc   = accecs, either 'r' or 'w'

      RETURNS
          0    = erverything fine 
          1    = error

     DESCRIPTION
          icopen uses the C 'fopen' to open a file for reading/writing.
          There can be up to 25 files opend at the same time.
          For a short description of the alogorithm see ictools(3).


     KNOWN PROBLEMS
          The filenames must be character*7.

     SEE ALSO
          icopen, icwinfo, icwrite, icskip, icrinfo, icread, icback, 
          icclose,ictools

